<number id="3DBCE93DC652FFB1CB8AFC3BFEBF20AF" box="[223,294,905,929]" pageId="8" pageNumber="44" value="29.5" valueMax="30.0" valueMin="29.0">29–30</number>
)
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BCBFB1AC652FFB1CBC2FC60FD41275B" blockId="8.[151,1436,977,1109]" pageId="8" pageNumber="44">
Two specimens have been seen from BCS, 
<quantity id="4C8C56FFC652FFB1C9C1FC63FD5020E7" box="[660,713,977,1001]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.609344" pageId="8" pageNumber="44" unit="mi" value="1.0">1 mi</quantity>
NE La Burrera, 
<geoCoordinate id="EE409DDDC652FFB1C8C6FC63FB8720E7" box="[915,1054,977,1001]" direction="north" orientation="latitude" pageId="8" pageNumber="44" precision="15" value="23.510555">
<number id="3DBCE93DC652FFB1C8C6FC63FC2820E7" box="[915,945,977,1001]" pageId="8" pageNumber="44" value="23.0">23</number>
° 
<number id="3DBCE93DC652FFB1C8EFFC63FC4020E7" box="[954,985,977,1001]" pageId="8" pageNumber="44" value="30.0">30</number>
’ 
<number id="3DBCE93DC652FFB1C88BFC63FC6520E7" box="[990,1020,977,1001]" pageId="8" pageNumber="44" value="38.0">38</number>
”N
</geoCoordinate>
, 
<geoCoordinate id="EE409DDDC652FFB1CF78FC63FB5320E7" box="[1069,1226,977,1001]" direction="west" orientation="longitude" pageId="8" pageNumber="44" precision="15" value="-110.04444">
<number id="3DBCE93DC652FFB1CF78FC63FBC120E7" box="[1069,1112,977,1001]" pageId="8" pageNumber="44" value="110.0">110</number>
°02’ 
<number id="3DBCE93DC652FFB1CFD1FC63FB3B20E7" box="[1156,1186,977,1001]" pageId="8" pageNumber="44" value="40.0">40</number>
”W
</geoCoordinate>
, 
<quantity id="4C8C56FFC652FFB1CF8DFC63FABC20E7" box="[1240,1317,977,1001]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" pageId="8" pageNumber="44" unit="m" value="500.0">500 m</quantity>
, on living twigs/small limbs 
<taxonomicName id="4C748099C652FFB1CA36FC47FDB72703" box="[355,558,1013,1037]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Acacia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="8" pageNumber="44" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="farnesiana">
<emphasis id="B9002708C652FFB1CA36FC47FDB72703" box="[355,558,1013,1037]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="44">Acacia farnesiana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(L.) Willd. (
<taxonomicName id="4C748099C652FFB1C9EFFC47FCB12703" box="[698,808,1013,1037]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="8" pageNumber="44" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Fabaceae</taxonomicName>
), 
<number id="3DBCE93DC652FFB1C86FFC47FCDE2703" box="[826,839,1013,1037]" pageId="8" pageNumber="44" value="5.0">5</number>
/ 
<date id="FFCADDDAC652FFB1C805FC47FC382703" box="[848,929,1013,1037]" pageId="8" pageNumber="44" value="1987-10-06">
<number id="3DBCE93DC652FFB1C805FC47FCC72703" box="[848,862,1013,1037]" pageId="8" pageNumber="44" value="6.0">6</number>
X- 
<number id="3DBCE93DC652FFB1C8D1FC47FC382703" box="[900,929,1013,1037]" pageId="8" pageNumber="44" value="87.0">87</number>
</date>
, R.L. Westcott, A.D. Mudge (
<collectionCode id="ED6563DFC652FFB1CFB9FC47FAD92703" box="[1260,1344,1013,1037]" pageId="8" pageNumber="44">RLWE</collectionCode>
); Ramal Los Naranjos, 
<quantity id="4C8C56FFC652FFB1CA6AFBABFE28273F" box="[319,433,1049,1073]" metricMagnitude="4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.4" metricValueMax="2.8" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="8" pageNumber="44" unit="km" value="24.0" valueMax="28.0" valueMin="20.0">20–28 km</quantity>
W Hwy. 1, 
<date id="FFCADDDAC652FFB1C96AFBABFD25273F" box="[575,700,1049,1073]" pageId="8" pageNumber="44" value="1994-08-28">
28-VIII- 
<number id="3DBCE93DC652FFB1C9CAFBABFD25273F" box="[671,700,1049,1073]" pageId="8" pageNumber="44" value="94.0">94</number>
</date>
, R.L. Turnbow (
<collectionCode id="ED6563DFC652FFB1C82FFBABFC57273F" box="[890,974,1049,1073]" pageId="8" pageNumber="44">RLWE</collectionCode>
). This species is widespread, often common, in 
<collectingCountry id="F363BB8AC652FFB1CBA6FB8FFED0275B" box="[243,329,1085,1109]" name="Mexico" pageId="8" pageNumber="44">Mexico</collectingCountry>
and is also known from 
<collectingCountry id="F363BB8AC652FFB1C90BFB8FFD4C275B" box="[606,725,1085,1109]" name="Nicaragua" pageId="8" pageNumber="44">Nicaragua</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BCBFB1AC652FFB1CBC2FB1BFEB727EA" blockId="8.[151,429,1193,1252]" pageId="8" pageNumber="44">
<taxonomicName id="4C748099C652FFB1CBC2FB1BFE3427CD" authority="Horn 1891" authorityName="Horn" authorityYear="1891" box="[151,429,1193,1219]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Agrilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="44" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="felix">
<emphasis id="B9002708C652FFB1CBC2FB1BFEBF27CC" box="[151,294,1193,1218]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="44">Agrilus felix</emphasis>
Horn 
<number id="3DBCE93DC652FFB1CA27FB1BFE3427CD" box="[370,429,1193,1219]" pageId="8" pageNumber="44" value="1891.0">1891</number>
</taxonomicName>
(Figs. 
<number id="3DBCE93DC652FFB1CB8AFB7EFEBF27EA" box="[223,294,1228,1252]" pageId="8" pageNumber="44" value="63.5" valueMax="64.0" valueMin="63.0">63–64</number>
)
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BCBFB1AC652FFB1CBC2FAA7FB342561" blockId="8.[151,1436,1300,1648]" pageId="8" pageNumber="44">
<bibRefCitation id="EFE586EBC652FFB1CBC2FAA7FEBA2622" author="Horn" box="[151,291,1300,1324]" pageId="8" pageNumber="44" refString="Horn, G. H. (1894) The Coleoptera of Baja California. Proceedings of the California Academy of Sciences, 4, 302 - 449." type="journal article" year="1894">
Horn (
<number id="3DBCE93DC652FFB1CBB5FAA6FE832622" box="[224,282,1300,1324]" pageId="8" pageNumber="44" value="1894.0">1894</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
first recorded this species from the peninsula. We have seen many specimens from the peninsula collected as far north as 
<quantity id="4C8C56FFC652FFB1CAD2FA85FE432641" box="[391,474,1335,1359]" metricMagnitude="4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.2874752" pageId="8" pageNumber="44" unit="mi" value="8.0">8 miles</quantity>
SW Rumarosa, near the California border and south into BCS. Probably the majority have been collected in the Vizcaíno Desert, to as far south as 
<quantity id="4C8C56FFC652FFB1C81DFAEEFC30267A" box="[840,937,1372,1396]" metricMagnitude="4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.414016" pageId="8" pageNumber="44" unit="mi" value="15.0">15 miles</quantity>
W of San Ignacio. The southernmost record for this species in Baja California is interesting: 
<collectingCountry id="F363BB8AC652FFB1C9E3FACDFD472699" box="[694,734,1407,1431]" name="Iceland" pageId="8" pageNumber="44">Isla</collectingCountry>
San Marcos, 
<date id="FFCADDDAC652FFB1C82DFACDFC7A2699" box="[888,995,1407,1431]" pageId="8" pageNumber="44" value="1952-06-22">
<number id="3DBCE93DC652FFB1C82DFACDFC0C2699" box="[888,917,1407,1431]" pageId="8" pageNumber="44" value="22.0">22</number>
-VI- 
<number id="3DBCE93DC652FFB1C893FACDFC7A2699" box="[966,995,1407,1431]" pageId="8" pageNumber="44" value="52.0">52</number>
</date>
, J.P. Figg-Hoblyn (
<collectionCode id="ED6563DFC652FFB1CFE9FACDFB612699" LSID="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34700" box="[1212,1272,1407,1431]" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15690" name="California Academy of Sciences" pageId="8" pageNumber="44">CAS</collectionCode>
). Dates of collection range from late March to late July, with the majority collected during April and May. In Baja California it has been taken on 
<taxonomicName id="4C748099C652FFB1CA32FA7AFE6A26EE" box="[359,499,1480,1504]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malvaceae" genus="Sphaeralcea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malvales" pageId="8" pageNumber="44" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9002708C652FFB1CA32FA7AFE6A26EE" box="[359,499,1480,1504]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="44">Sphaeralcea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
spp. (
<taxonomicName id="4C748099C652FFB1C962FA75FD2D26D1" box="[567,692,1479,1503]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malvaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malvales" pageId="8" pageNumber="44" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Malvaceae</taxonomicName>
) and by beating 
<taxonomicName id="4C748099C652FFB1C825FA7BFBCE26EE" box="[880,1111,1480,1504]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Prosopis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Fabales" pageId="8" pageNumber="44" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="glandulosa">
<emphasis id="B9002708C652FFB1C825FA7BFBCE26EE" box="[880,1111,1480,1504]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="44">Prosopis glandulosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicName id="4C748099C652FFB1CF0BFA7BFB6226EE" box="[1118,1275,1481,1504]" pageId="8" pageNumber="44" rank="variety" variety="torreyana">
var. 
<emphasis id="B9002708C652FFB1CFDBFA7BFB6226EE" box="[1166,1275,1481,1504]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="44">torreyana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Elsewhere in 
<collectingCountry id="F363BB8AC652FFB1CBC2FA5EFF75250A" box="[151,236,1516,1540]" name="Mexico" pageId="8" pageNumber="44">Mexico</collectingCountry>
it has been recorded only from Sonora and Chihuahua. It occurs widely in the western 
<collectingCountry id="F363BB8AC652FFB1CF9FFA5EFB67250A" box="[1226,1278,1516,1540]" name="United States of America" pageId="8" pageNumber="44">U.S.</collectingCountry>
, as far east as Colorado and Texas. Larval hosts are recorded from several plants in 
<taxonomicName id="4C748099C652FFB1C8F2F9BDFBF92529" box="[935,1120,1551,1575]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Chenopodiaceae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="8" pageNumber="44" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Chenopodiaceae</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C748099C652FFB1CFCDF9BDFA9A2529" box="[1176,1283,1551,1575]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="8" pageNumber="44" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Fabaceae</taxonomicName>
, and utilizing such disparate host families seems strange, although specimens reared from legumes may instead be 
<taxonomicName id="4C748099C652FFB1CE48F986FF472561" authority="Knull." authorityName="Knull." class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Agrilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="44" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hualpaii">
<emphasis id="B9002708C652FFB1CE48F986FA052542" box="[1309,1436,1588,1612]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="44">A. hualpaii</emphasis>
Knull.
</taxonomicName>
Adults have also been collected on 
<taxonomicName id="4C748099C652FFB1C924F9EAFBBD2561" authority="(A. Gray) Rydb." authorityName="(A. Gray) Rydb." box="[625,1060,1623,1648]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Psorothamnus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="8" pageNumber="44" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="emoryi">
<emphasis id="B9002708C652FFB1C924F9EAFCFE257E" box="[625,871,1624,1648]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="44">Psorothamnus emoryi</emphasis>
(A. Gray) Rydb.
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName id="4C748099C652FFB1CF67F9E5FB382561" box="[1074,1185,1623,1647]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="8" pageNumber="44" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Fabaceae</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
